Democratic challenger Joe Biden has expressed optimism with the United States Presidential Election, saying his team is on the right track to win the poll. He addressed supporters earlier at his hometown in Wilmington Delaware, calling for patience as vote counting continues. “Your patience is commendable…we feel good about where we are, we are on track to win this election”. Biden says he is confident about key states including Arizona, Minnesota and Georgia. Biden needs to win the states of Michigan, Wisconsin and Pennsylvania that sent Republican Donald Trump to the White House in 2016 for possible breakthroughs. In the video below, Biden addresses supporters as vote counting continues: 